      "date": "2014-11-20 00:43:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Oleg,\n\n         do_nodes $nodes \"rc=0;\n val=\\\\\\$($LCTL get_param -n catastrophe 2>&1);\n if [[ \\\\\\$? -eq 0 && \\\\\\$val -ne 0 ]]; then\n         echo \\\\\\$(hostname -s): \\\\\\$val;\n         rc=\\\\\\$val;\n fi\n exit \\\\\\$rc\"\n\nOnly when the output of \"$LCTL get_param -n catastrophe\" is not equal to 0, check_catastrophe() will fail.\n\nCould you please check the test output at the end of each sub-test to see what the $val is? Thank you.",
